+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772755100814,"sessionID":"ses_33f8feb1dffeT17saeJkljdm3R","part":{"id":"prt_cc0702329001U7VoUspqhJY74J","sessionID":"ses_33f8feb1dffeT17saeJkljdm3R","messageID":"msg_cc0701fb7002SdjiYdd4JtmLNa","type":"tool","callID":"60ac071e6","tool":"write","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","content":"---\n# Ralph Plan for Reactive Spreadsheet Engine\n---\n\n## Original Request\nBuild a TypeScript library implementing a reactive spreadsheet engine with the following features:\n- Cell values (numbers, strings, booleans, formulas)\n- Formula parsing supporting arithmetic, parentheses, cell references, comparison operators, and built‑in functions (`SUM`, `AVERAGE`, `MIN`, `MAX`, `COUNT`, `IF`).\n- Range handling (`A1:B2` style).\n- Automatic reactive updates when dependent cells change.\n- Circular reference detection with error throwing.\n- Export a `Spreadsheet` class from `src/index.ts` exposing:\n  ```ts\n  set(cell:string, value:string|number|boolean):void\n  get(cell:string): string|number|boolean|null\n  getDisplay(cell:string): string\n  getCells(): Map<string, any>\n  ```\n- Provide comprehensive Vitest tests.\n- Typescript project with appropriate `tsconfig.json` and npm scripts.\n\n## Goal\nA fully functional, typed TypeScript library that meets the API contract, correctly evaluates formulas, updates dependents reactively, detects circular dependencies, and passes all provided and hidden tests.\n\n## Approach (Step‑by‑Step)\n1. **Project Scaffold**\n   - Create `src/` folder files: `Spreadsheet.ts`, `Parser.ts`, `Evaluator.ts`, `DependencyGraph.ts`, `functions.ts`, and `index.ts` that re‑exports `Spreadsheet`.\n2. **Cell Reference & Range Utilities**\n   - Implement helpers to convert column letters ↔ indices, parse cell IDs, and expand ranges into cell lists.\n3. **Parser**\n   - Write a lightweight recursive‑descent parser (or use a simple shunting‑yard) to transform formula strings into an AST supporting:\n     - Literals (numbers, strings, booleans)\n     - Binary operators `+ - * / > < >= <= = <>`\n     - Parentheses\n     - CellReference nodes\n     - FunctionCall nodes with argument list (including range arguments).\n4. **Evaluator**\n   - Walk the AST, fetching cell values from the `Spreadsheet` instance.\n   - Implement built‑in functions (`SUM`, `AVERAGE`, `MIN`, `MAX`, `COUNT`, `IF`).\n   - Coerce types as needed, return `null` for empty cells.\n5. **Dependency Graph**\n   - For each formula, determine dependent cells (cell references and cells inside ranges).\n   - Store a directed graph (Map<string, Set<string>> of dependents). When a cell changes, perform a topological sort / BFS to recompute affected cells.\n   - Detect cycles during graph updates; throw an error if a new edge would create a cycle.\n6. **Spreadsheet Class**\n   - `set` stores raw value or formula string, updates internal maps, builds/updates dependency graph, and triggers recomputation of dependents.\n   - `get` returns computed value (or `null`). `getDisplay` returns stringified value.\n   - `getCells` returns a `Map` of all non‑empty computed cells.\n7. **Testing**\n   - Write Vitest suite under `test/` covering:\n     - Simple literals, arithmetic, parentheses.\n     - Cell references and reactive updates.\n     - Each built‑in function with range handling.\n     - Comparison operators and `IF`.\n     - Circular dependency detection.\n     - Edge cases (empty cells, non‑numeric in SUM, string quoting, Boolean handling).\n8. **Packaging**\n   - Ensure `tsconfig.json` includes `src/**/*.ts`.\n   - Add npm scripts (`test`, `build`).\n   - Update `package.json` if needed.\n\n## Key Files\n- `src/Spreadsheet.ts` – main class, orchestrates parsing/evaluation & graph.\n- `src/Parser.ts` – tokeniser & parser producing AST.\n- `src/Evaluator.ts` – evaluates AST against a cell value provider.\n- `src/DependencyGraph.ts` – manages edges, cycle detection, recompute order.\n- `src/functions.ts` – implementations of built‑in functions.\n- `src/utils.ts` – cell reference/range helpers.\n- `src/index.ts` – export `Spreadsheet`.\n- `test/spreadsheet.test.ts` – Vitest tests.\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n- **Circular detection complexity** – Use depth‑first search on insertion; abort before committing edge.\n- **Formula parsing bugs** – Keep parser small and well‑tested via unit tests for each token/operator.\n- **Range expansion performance** – Ranges are modest (typical spreadsheet size); simple loop is acceptable.\n- **Type coercion** – Explicitly handle numbers vs strings vs booleans; follow JavaScript truthiness rules for `IF`.\n- **Reactive recompute order** – Use topological sort; fallback to iterative propagation with visited guard.\n\n## Milestones\n- [ ] Scaffold source files & utils.\n- [ ] Implement parser & AST.\n- [ ] Implement built‑in functions.\n- [ ] Build dependency graph with cycle detection.\n- [ ] Complete `Spreadsheet` methods.\n- [ ] Write full test suite.\n- [ ] Verify `npm test` passes.\n\n---\n","encoding":"utf-8"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772755100799,"end":1772755100812}}}}
